<subSubSection pageId="139" pageNumber="140" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 132" captionStartId="F132" captionText="Figure 132. Distribution of Conostegia rubiginosa." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure132" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96490" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">132</figureCitation>
). West coast of Colombia, sea level to 100 m elevation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
For the few specimens studied, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Gleason" authorityYear="1945" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia rubiginosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubiginosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia rubiginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite variable in leaf size and consistency. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Gleason" authorityYear="1945" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia rubiginosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubiginosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia rubiginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Markgraf" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia centronioides" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="centronioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia centronioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia lasiopoda" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lasiopoda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia lasiopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia rufescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Markgraf" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia centronioides" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="centronioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia centronioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it can be distinguish by the larger flowers without a constriction in the hypanthium, and denser reddish indument. From 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia rufescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it can be distinguished by its exserted style. For differences between this species and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia lasiopoda" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lasiopoda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia lasiopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see the discussion under the latter.
</paragraph>
